The paper deals with face anti-spoofing, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation benchmarks are based on public datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
